// Spreadsheet Manager
// CRUD operations for spreadsheet files (.spreadsheet.json) stored in a configurable base directory.

An in-memory index (Map of id -> SpreadsheetMeta) is maintained after initialization.
Spreadsheet IDs are derived from filenames by stripping the .spreadsheet.json extension.
Content must be valid JSON and within config.MAX_FILE_SIZE.

FUNCTION constructor(basePath)
  Accept an optional basePath override; otherwise use the configured default.

---

FUNCTION initialize() -> void
  Ensure the base directory exists.
  Scan for all .spreadsheet.json files, stat each one, and populate the in-memory index.

---

FUNCTION listSpreadsheets() -> SpreadsheetListItem[]
  Return an array of { id, name, lastModified } for each indexed spreadsheet.

---

FUNCTION getSpreadsheet(id) -> Spreadsheet | null
  Look up in index; return null if not found. Read and return the spreadsheet content.

---

FUNCTION saveSpreadsheet(id, content) -> void
  Throw if id not in index or content exceeds MAX_FILE_SIZE.
  Validate that content is valid JSON (throw if not).
  Write to disk and update lastModified in the index.

---

FUNCTION createSpreadsheet(name, content) -> string
  Sanitize name to form id. Throw if id exists, content is too large, or content is invalid JSON.
  Write the file and add to index. Return the id.

---

FUNCTION deleteSpreadsheet(id) -> void
  Throw if id not in index. Delete the file from disk. Remove from index.

---

FUNCTION updateIndex(id, path) -> void
  Asynchronously stat the path and upsert the index entry. Logs error on failure.

---

FUNCTION removeFromIndex(id) -> void
  Delete the id from the in-memory index without touching the filesystem.

---

FUNCTION reset() -> void
  Clear the entire in-memory index. Caller must call initialize() to rebuild.
